.TH CLONE 5 "" "" "Inferno Reference "
.PP
.SH NAME
clone \- duplicate a fid
.PP
.SH SYNOPSIS
.IP
.EX
Tclone tag [2] fid [2] newfid [2]
Rclone tag [2] fid [2]
.EE
.PP
.SH DESCRIPTION
The Tclone request carries as arguments an existing 
.I fid
and a proposed 
.I newfid
(which must not be in use) that the client wishes to associate with the same file as 
.I fid
.
The 
.I fid
must be valid in the current session and must not have been opened for I/O by an 
.I open
or 
.I create
message.
After a successful 
.I clone
, and before any subsequent messages, 
.I fid
and 
.I newfid
are indistinguishable.
.PP
.SH ENTRY POINTS
A 
.I clone
message is generated by any system call that evaluates a path name and by a 
.I read
of a union directory.
